  "body": "We can use className prop on any HTML element but not an a custom react component. Requesting to support this feature as it simplifies the component usage when there is a need to apply additional styles without having to wrap the component in an external DIV.\n\n```\n//MyComponent\nrender() {\n   return <div className=\"message\">Hello!</div>;\n}\n\n//expected usage\n<MyComponent className=\"message--blue\"/>\n\nshould render \n<div className=\"message message--blue\">Hello!</div>\n```\n\nThis affect can be achieved by a mixin but non-mounted tests cannot use this.props.className to find the components.\n\n```\ncomponentDidMount() {\nif (this.props.className) {\n   ReactDOM.findDOMNode(this).classList.add(this.props.className);\n}\n}\n```\n",
